==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[cor]]'' (horn) + ''[[anglais]]'' (English)

===Noun===
'''[[cor]] [[anglais]]'''

# A double reed [[woodwind]] [[instrument]] in the [[oboe]] family that is pitched in F, a fifth lower than the oboe and is consequently approximately one-third longer than the oboe.

====Synonyms====
*[[English horn]]

